Pre-Game Insights: Guinea have an unbeaten start to the competition
Senegal have booked their spot in the knockout round
Guinea need at least a point to seal their berth in the knockout stage
Others: The National Elephants recorded their first win at the AFCON in five games on Saturday
Captain Naby Keïta made an appearance from the bench after recovering from a thigh injury and is expected to start here
Moussa Niakhaté suffered an injury in the campaign opener while Abdallah Sima was injured in training last week
Senegal have the best attacking record in the group stage of the competition, scoring three goals apiece in two games
